resources.string:
The active user report is generally called when users log in successfully.
You can log in to the console, and go to Mobile Analysis > Basic analysis > Basic dashboard > Behavior analysis to view active users.

userId of this device: %1$s
Other logs can be queried by using this id
The whitelist feature of Mobile Delivery Service (including features such as version update and hotpatch) also requires this id for configuration purpose.
Tap this to trigger a crash.\nYou can log in to the console, and go to Mobile Analysis > Performance analysis > Crash report to view it.

After the page is opened, the display of all components and taps of all buttons will be reported through the automation log.\nYou can log in to the console, and go to Mobile Analysis > Basic analysis > Page analysis > Behavior analysis to view it.

Except for performance logs (crash, hangup, frozen) that are reported in real time, other logs are reported based on specific policies. Tap this button to trigger an active report.\nYou can log in to the console, and go to Mobile Analysis > Log management > Query history log to view it
After you enable the crash on launch feature, when you close and relaunch an app, a crash on launch will be simulated. The log will be reported after 30 seconds.
Tap this to trigger a period of ANR.\nYou can log in to the console, and go to Mobile Analysis > Performance analysis > Frozen report to view it.
Tap this to trigger a period of hangup.\nYou can log in to the console, and go to Mobile Analysis > Performance analysis > Hangup report to view it.
